data.picked:
"That movie was not interesting, did it?"
In this sentence, "面白く" (maezaki) means "interesting" or "pleasant to watch", and "ないですか" (nai desu ka) is a question particle that is used to ask for confirmation or agreement. So the sentence as a whole can be translated as "Was the movie not interesting?" or "Didn't the movie hold your interest?"
